Students organisation Sasco says it supports a call for a national shutdown of tertiary institutions. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African Students Congress hasn't ruled out a national shutdown at tertiary institutions. The student organisation wants historical debt scrapped to allow students to register. READ: NSFAS students don't have to pay registration: Nzimande Chaos broke out at the University of KwaZulu Natal after students were prevented from registering until a portion of the money owed is paid.